            <h1>SuperControl Listing Site Demo Tutorial</h1>
            <p class="lead">Build a listing and property-detail MVC experience backed by SuperControl index and listing endpoints with deterministic delta-based cache invalidation.</p>
        </header>

        <section class="sv-doc">
            <h2>What you are building</h2>
            <p>Two routes power the experience:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><code>/supercontrol-listing-site-demo</code> (search and listing cards)</li>
                <li><code>/supercontrol-listing-site-demo/property/{propertyId}</code> (property detail)</li>
            </ul>
            <p>The runtime flow is:</p>
            <ol>
                <li>Pull account indexes from SuperControl.</li>
                <li>Resolve each property payload URL from index entries.</li>
                <li>Hydrate cards and detail views with listing, prices, availability, and configuration data.</li>
                <li>Cache payloads using index <code>lastUpdated</code> as the invalidation key.</li>
            </ol>
        </section>

        <section class="sv-doc">
            <h2>Prerequisites</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>.NET 10 SDK</li>
                <li>SuperControl API token</li>
                <li>SuperControl account ID</li>
                <li>(Optional) SuperControl calendar embed key for the detail page widget</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="sv-doc">
            <h2>Source code and build</h2>
            <p>Public repository: <a class="text-link" href="https://github.com/petergraves-dot/SuperControlApiDemo" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">github.com/petergraves-dot/SuperControlApiDemo</a></p>
            <p>Checkout and build:</p>
            <pre class="sc-pre">git clone https://github.com/petergraves-dot/SuperControlApiDemo.git
cd SuperControlApiDemo
dotnet restore supercontrol-listing-site-demo-public.sln
dotnet build supercontrol-listing-site-demo-public.sln</pre>
            <p>Run locally:</p>
            <pre class="sc-pre">dotnet run --project supercontrol-listing-site-demo.csproj</pre>
        </section>

        <section class="sv-doc">
            <h2>Environment configuration</h2>
                        <p>Set these values in <code>appsettings.json</code>:</p>
                        <pre class="sc-pre">"SuperControl": {
    "ApiKey": "your-supercontrol-sc-token",
    "AccountId": 22263,
    "BaseUrl": "https://api.supercontrol.co.uk/v3/",
    "CalendarKey": "your-supercontrol-calendar-key",
    "DefaultPropertyId": 671777
}</pre>
                        <p>Environment variables can override appsettings values in production (for example <code>SuperControl__ApiKey</code>).</p>
                        <p>For listing and property routes, both <code>ApiKey</code> and <code>AccountId</code> must be configured. <code>CalendarKey</code> is optional and only required to render the embedded calendar widget.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="sv-doc">
            <h2>Dependency injection wiring</h2>
            <p><code>Program.cs</code> registers these services:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><code>AddOptions&lt;SuperControlOptions&gt;().Bind(...)</code></li>
                <li><code>AddMemoryCache()</code></li>
                <li><code>AddSingleton&lt;ISuperControlResponseCache, SuperControlResponseCache&gt;()</code></li>
                <li><code>AddHttpClient&lt;ISuperControlClient, SuperControlClient&gt;(...)</code></li>
                <li><code>AddScoped&lt;ISuperControlListingSiteService, SuperControlListingSiteService&gt;()</code></li>
            </ul>
            <p><code>SuperControlClient</code> sends the <code>SC-TOKEN</code> auth header with each request.</p>
            <p>Code example:</p>
            <pre class="sc-pre">builder.Services
    .AddOptions&lt;SuperControlOptions&gt;()
    .Bind(builder.Configuration.GetSection(SuperControlOptions.SectionName));

builder.Services.AddMemoryCache();
builder.Services.AddHttpClient&lt;ISuperControlClient, SuperControlClient&gt;((sp, httpClient) =&gt;
{
    var options = sp.GetRequiredService&lt;IOptions&lt;SuperControlOptions&gt;&gt;().Value;
    if (Uri.TryCreate(options.BaseUrl, UriKind.Absolute, out var baseAddress))
    {
        httpClient.BaseAddress = baseAddress;
    }
    httpClient.Timeout = TimeSpan.FromSeconds(30);
});

builder.Services.AddScoped&lt;ISuperControlListingSiteService, SuperControlListingSiteService&gt;();</pre>
        </section>

        <section class="sv-doc">
            <h2>Endpoints used</h2>
            <p>The listing page calls three indexes in parallel:</p>
            <ol>
                <li><code>GET /properties/contentindex/{accountId}</code></li>
                <li><code>GET /properties/pricesindex/{accountId}</code></li>
                <li><code>GET /properties/availabilityindex/{accountId}</code></li>
            </ol>
            <p>Then, for each property, it follows each index <code>listingUrl</code> to fetch payloads:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>listing payload</li>
                <li>prices payload</li>
                <li>availability payload</li>
            </ul>
            <p>The property detail route also loads:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><code>GET /properties/configurationindex/{accountId}</code></li>
                <li><code>configurationContentUrl</code> for full property configuration payload</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

