        <section class="sv-doc">
            <h2>Listing page behavior</h2>
            <p><code>SuperControlListingSiteDemoController</code> binds query parameters (<code>where</code>, <code>checkIn</code>, <code>checkOut</code>, and <code>guests</code>) into <code>SuperControlListingSiteDemoRequestViewModel</code>.</p>
            <p>The controller delegates to <code>SuperControlListingSiteDemoViewModelFactory</code>, which validates configuration and clamps guests to <code>1..30</code> before calling:</p>
            <pre class="sc-pre">_listingSiteService.BuildSnapshotAsync(accountId, Where, Guests, CheckIn, CheckOut, cancellationToken)</pre>
            <p><code>BuildSnapshotAsync</code> loads indexes in parallel, filters active properties, hydrates listing cards, enriches with prices and availability, and returns a sorted <code>SuperControlListingSiteSnapshot</code>.</p>
            <p>Factory orchestration example:</p>
            <pre class="sc-pre">var normalizedRequest = request with { Guests = Math.Clamp(request.Guests, 1, 30) };

var snapshot = await _listingSiteService.BuildSnapshotAsync(
    accountId,
    normalizedRequest.Where,
    normalizedRequest.Guests,
    normalizedRequest.CheckIn,
    normalizedRequest.CheckOut,
    cancellationToken);</pre>
            <p>Service orchestration example:</p>
            <pre class="sc-pre">var contentIndexUrl = ResolveIndexUrl(account.ContentIndexUrl, $"properties/contentindex/{account.AccountId}");
var pricesIndexUrl = ResolveIndexUrl(account.PricesIndexUrl, $"properties/pricesindex/{account.AccountId}");
var availabilityIndexUrl = ResolveIndexUrl(account.AvailabilityIndexUrl, $"properties/availabilityindex/{account.AccountId}");

var contentTask = GetTypedByUrlAsync&lt;ContentIndexResponse&gt;(contentIndexUrl, ...);
var pricesIndexTask = GetTypedByUrlAsync&lt;PricesIndexResponse&gt;(pricesIndexUrl, ...);
var availabilityIndexTask = GetTypedByUrlAsync&lt;AvailabilityIndexResponse&gt;(availabilityIndexUrl, ...);

await Task.WhenAll(contentTask, pricesIndexTask, availabilityIndexTask);</pre>
        </section>

        <section class="sv-doc">
            <h2>Property detail behavior</h2>
            <p><code>SuperControlPropertyController</code> receives the route <code>{propertyId:int}</code> and query fields, then calls <code>SuperControlPropertyViewModelFactory</code>.</p>
            <p>The factory validates configuration, clamps guests to <code>1..30</code>, and loads one property by id using:</p>
            <pre class="sc-pre">_listingSiteService.GetPropertyDetailAsync(accountId, PropertyId, Guests, CheckIn, CheckOut, cancellationToken)</pre>
            <p>The detail model combines listing, prices, availability, and configuration data to render gallery, amenities, availability status, sample rates, rules, occupancy, and payment forms.</p>
            <p>Detail call pattern:</p>
            <pre class="sc-pre">var result = await _listingSiteService.GetPropertyDetailAsync(
    accountId,
    PropertyId,
    Guests,
    CheckIn,
    CheckOut,
    cancellationToken);

Property = result.Property;
Error = result.Error;</pre>
        </section>

        <section class="sv-doc">
            <h2>Delta cache strategy</h2>
            <p><code>GetDeltaCachedPropertyPayloadAsync&lt;T&gt;</code> stores payloads under <code>.supercontrol-cache/{payloadType}</code>.</p>
            <ol>
                <li>Read <code>*.meta.json</code>.</li>
                <li>If <code>meta.lastUpdatedUtc</code> matches index <code>lastUpdated</code>, return local payload (hit).</li>
                <li>If changed, fetch from API and overwrite body + metadata (miss).</li>
                <li>If API fetch fails and local body exists, return stale cached payload (stale fallback hit).</li>
            </ol>
            <p>Metadata tracks <code>url</code>, <code>lastUpdatedUtc</code>, and <code>cachedAtUtc</code>.</p>
            <p>Cache implementation example:</p>
            <pre class="sc-pre">if (cachedMeta is not null
    &amp;&amp; cachedMeta.LastUpdatedUtc == normalizedLastUpdated
    &amp;&amp; File.Exists(bodyPath))
{
    var cachedBody = await File.ReadAllTextAsync(bodyPath, cancellationToken);
    var cachedPayload = Deserialize&lt;T&gt;(cachedBody);
    if (cachedPayload is not null)
    {
        return new DeltaCachedPayloadResult&lt;T&gt;(cachedPayload, CacheDisposition.Hit);
    }
}

var response = await _client.GetByUrlAsync(payloadUrl, cancellationToken);
if (response.IsSuccess)
{
    await File.WriteAllTextAsync(bodyPath, response.Body, cancellationToken);
    await File.WriteAllTextAsync(metaPath, JsonSerializer.Serialize(new DeltaCacheMetadata
    {
        Url = payloadUrl,
        LastUpdatedUtc = normalizedLastUpdated,
        CachedAtUtc = DateTime.UtcNow
    }), cancellationToken);
}</pre>
            <p>Metadata file shape:</p>
            <pre class="sc-pre">{
  "url": "https://api.supercontrol.co.uk/v3/properties/listing/123456",
  "lastUpdatedUtc": "2026-03-28T18:11:54Z",
  "cachedAtUtc": "2026-03-28T18:14:02Z"
}</pre>
        </section>

        <section class="sv-doc">
            <h2>Availability and pricing parsing examples</h2>
            <p>Availability is read from a day-series string where <code>Y</code> means available.</p>
            <pre class="sc-pre">private static bool IsRangeAvailable(DateTime seriesStartUtcDate, string series, DateTime startUtcDate, DateTime endUtcDateExclusive)
{
    var fromIndex = (int)(startUtcDate - seriesStartUtcDate).TotalDays;
    var nights = (int)(endUtcDateExclusive - startUtcDate).TotalDays;
    if (fromIndex &lt; 0 || nights &lt;= 0) return false;
    if (fromIndex + nights &gt; series.Length) return false;

    for (var i = fromIndex; i &lt; fromIndex + nights; i++)
    {
        if (series[i] != 'Y') return false;
    }

    return true;
}</pre>
            <p>Price LOS rows are parsed from CSV-like strings (<code>date,pax,los1,los2,los3,...</code>):</p>
            <pre class="sc-pre">var parts = row.Split(',', StringSplitOptions.TrimEntries | StringSplitOptions.RemoveEmptyEntries);
if (!DateOnly.TryParse(parts[0], out var date)) return null;

decimal? min = null;
var bestNights = 0;
for (var i = 2; i &lt; parts.Length; i++)
{
    if (!decimal.TryParse(parts[i], NumberStyles.Number, CultureInfo.InvariantCulture, out var price) || price &lt;= 0)
    {
        continue;
    }
    var nights = i - 1;
    if (min is null || price &lt; min.Value)
    {
        min = price;
        bestNights = nights;
    }
}</pre>
        </section>

